Title: This video predates Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modiâ€™s call for COVID-19 vigils
Narrative_Description: Brazilians showed solidarity with PM Modi's solidarity vigil in India against the coronavirus
Motive_Descripion: To gain praise for PM Modi's efforts in fighting COVID-19 and building solidarity among people
Summary: People circulated a video from Brazil that predated PM Modi's call for a vigil from home and tried to claim that the video was of Brazilians having a vigil in solidarity with India and Modi

Title: This image of a newspaper front page has been doctored
Narrative_Description: Indian Muslim leader donated to PM Modi's COVID-19 relief fund
Motive_Descripion: Project communal solidarity
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Muslims, Narendra Modi, relief fund, donation
Summary: Doctored newspaper clippings were circulated to claim that an Indian Muslim leader had donated to PM Modi's COVID-19 relief fund

Title: This video was uploaded to an Indian wrestling-themed YouTube channel in June 2019
Narrative_Description: A policeman was thrashed inside a temple for trying to enforce the lockdown
Motive_Descripion: Criticize Delhi CM, Arvind Kejriwal, for not taking action
Summary: An old video was circulated as a video of a policeman being beaten up by people inside a temple for trying to enforce the Indian lockdown

Title: This video of a Sanskrit teacher was recorded in London in November 2019
Narrative_Description: A Spanish radio host was reciting Sanskrit verses on the radio amidst the coronavirus pandemic
Motive_Descripion: Make it seem like Indian culture was being used widely to instill hope in people
Summary: Videos of a London-based Sanskrit-teacher were shared on social media with the false claim that she was a Spanish-radio host who was reciting Sanskrit verses to instill hope during the pandemic

Title: WHO did not warn against eating cabbage during the COVID-19 pandemic
Narrative_Description: Coronavirus can survive in cabbages for really long and people should not eat it
Motive_Descripion: Scare people into not eating cabbages
Summary: False claims were circulated on social media saying that the WHO had said coronavirus survives in cabbage for a long time and so we should not eat cabbage during the pandemic

Title: Indian authorities refute 'fake' claim about food markets closing in Chennai during COVID-19 lockdown
Narrative_Description: The government had shut down the food markets in Chennai, Tamil Nadu
Motive_Descripion: Scare people into thinking food markets will also be shut
Summary: Rumors were spread saying that all food markets would also be closed during the lockdown in Chennai

Title: Indian health authorities refute myth that juiced vegetables can cure COVID-19
Narrative_Description: Juiced vegetables can cure COVID-19
Motive_Descripion: Make people think there is a cure to coronavirus
Summary: Fake remedy was circulated over social media saying that juiced vegetables could help cure coronavirus

Title: These photos have circulated since 2011 in reports about the Indian yoga guru being hospitalised after a nine-day fast
Narrative_Description: Popular yoga guru was admitted to the hospital after drinking cow urine to prevent coronavirus
Motive_Descripion: Mock yoga guru, Baba Ramdev
Key_Words: Coronavirus, cow urine, yoga, Baba Ramdev, hospital, cure
Summary: Old pictures of Baba Ramdev from 2011 were circulated as recent images of him being hospitalized after drinking cow urine to prevent coronavirus

Title: This video shows a lodging facility that was converted into a COVID-19 quarantine centre
Narrative_Description: A temple was converted into a quarantine center
Motive_Descripion: Stoke religious anger by making people think the government had turned a temple into a quarantine center
Key_Words: Coronavirus, temple, Andhra Pradesh, Kanipakam Ganesh temple, YS Jagan Mohan Reddy
Summary: A video was circulated over social media with the claim that a temple in Andhra Pradesh had been converted into a quarantine facility and blamed Andhra CM Jagan Mohan Reddy

Title: This video has circulated online since 2009 -- more than one decade before the COVID-19 pandemic
Narrative_Description: A freight train was carrying essential commodities to be delivered to people during the coronavirus pandemic
Motive_Descripion: Generate praise for PM Modi and his efforts to fight coronavirus
Key_Words: Coronavirus, essential commodities, Narendra Modi, freight train
Summary: An old video was circulated on social media as a video of a freight train distributing essential commodities during the coronavirus pandemic

Title: Indian health experts say there is no evidence of link between novel coronavirus transmission and specific food items
Narrative_Description: The coronavirus can be spread through a worm found in food and drinks
Motive_Descripion: Stoke fear among people
Summary: Messages circulating on social media spread a false rumor that coronavirus was spreading through a worm, being found in certain foods and drinks, which people should avoid consuming

Title: The Indian Health Ministry said it did not issue this 'emergency warning' via text message
Narrative_Description: The coronavirus was spreading in India rapidly and the Indian Health Ministry had prescribed certain precautions to prevent catching the virus
Motive_Descripion: Stoke fear and also provide false hope through fake precautions and cures
Summary: A message circulated under fake authority of the Indian Health Ministry claimed severity and fatality of the virus and claimed that certain precautionary methods could be taken to prevent catching the virus

Title: This video shows workmen uncovering a bat-infested roof in the US state of Florida in 2011
Narrative_Description: Chrysanthemum bats were the origin of the virus in Hubei, China
Motive_Descripion: Pin origin of the virus on bat infestations in China
Summary: An image of bat infestation was circulated with the false claim that the coronavirus originated due to bats in Hubei, China

Title: Indian officials say novel coronavirus has not been found in poultry
Narrative_Description: Coronavirus was found in poultry
Motive_Descripion: Make people afraid of consuming poultry
Summary: Fake rumors circulated claiming that coronavirus is found in poultry

Title: Indian health authorities dismiss hoax report of novel coronavirus case in east Indian state
Narrative_Description: Emergence of the first cases of coronavirus in different regions
Motive_Descripion: Make people afraid of the presence of coronavirus
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Bihar, Purnea, Uttar Pradesh, meat, fish
Summary: Multiple rumors emerged from different parts of the country at different times (cited here: Bihar, Uttar Pradesh) of the emergence of patient zero in the states. Posts also claimed that doctors were advising people to not consume fish or meat products

Title: Experts in India refute misleading claim that China-made Holi festival goods are infected with coronavirus
Narrative_Description: China sent over goods related to an Indian festival that were riddled with the coronavirus
Motive_Descripion: Discredit and blame China
Summary: Fake rumors circulated claiming that China had sent over goods to India that had the coronavirus on them

Title: UNICEF officials refute false claim that agency released coronavirus prevention guidelines
Narrative_Description: UNICEF released guidelines to prevent the coronavirus
Motive_Descripion: Make people think there are precautionary and preventative measures for coronavirus
Summary: In India, a message and image of fake UNICEF guidelines was circulated that contained numerous false claims about the nature of the virus and false methods of preventing it, that sometimes also downplayed the severity of the virus

Title: These photos show Indiaâ€™s annual cow dung festival in October 2019 -- weeks before the coronavirus outbreak
Narrative_Description: Bathing in cow dung will prevent coronavirus
Motive_Descripion: Make people believe a ridiculous claim that cow dung can prevent the virus
Summary: Old images of the cow dung festival from October 2019 were shared as people bathing in cow dung to prevent the coronavirus

Title: This footage has circulated in reports about conditions in a COVID-19 ward at a hospital in Mumbai
Narrative_Description: Mismanagement of patients at Delhi hospitals treating COVID-19 patients
Motive_Descripion: Blame Delhi government for bad management of patients at hospitals
Summary: A misleading video of a hospital with dead bodies lying around was peddled as a Delhi hospital, when it was a hospital in Mumbai

Title: Misinformation circulates about resignation of nurses at Indian hospital during pandemic
Narrative_Description: Nurses resigned from hospital during the pandemic due to mistreatment by Muslim patients
Motive_Descripion: Communalize the issue
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Tablighi Jamaat, nurses, resignation, hospital
Summary: A news bulletin was misrepresented and circulated online to claim that nurses had resigned at an Indian hospital due to mistreatment by Muslim patients
